    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In synchronous messaging a sender blocks until the receiver acknowledges; in asynchronous messaging the sender fires a message into a queue and immediately returns to doing other work. The receiver picks up the message when it is ready. This temporal decoupling is what gives multi-agent systems their throughput \u2014 a slow downstream agent no longer stalls the rest of the pipeline."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Async Messaging Pattern",
          "title": "Sender enqueues a message and continues; receivers dequeue independently"
        }
      },
